stimulus:
Welcome! This experiment will last ~1 hour. In this experiment, you are the head captain of a pirate ship traveling around the world to different places. You will complete several different tasks during this experiment. Here is an overview of these tasks:


1. Tutorial and quiz

2. Pick a pirate game in 6 different places

3. Pick a pirate game and memory game

4. Final questions and payment


If you complete the entire experiment, you will receive $15 and you can earn up to $3 in bonus payments.

[Press the space bar to begin the tutorial]

You are the head captain of a pirate ship. Pirates rob other ships like the one below as they leave they leave the marketplace port. Ships leaving have just sold all their goods at the marketplace, so they have lots of gold on them.

[Press the space bar to continue]

As the head captain, you do not have to rob any ships yourself. You get to choose which pirate you want to rob the next ship. If they are successful at robbing the ship, then you will get gold coins. If they are not successful, then you will get no gold coins.

The more coins you collect, the more bonus money you will win. So choose your pirates wisely.

[Press the space bar to continue]

Even the most skilled pirate will not be able to rob EVERY ship. Some ships will have very strong defenses against attacks.For example, blue beard, here, is very good at robbing ships.

You can press the ‘1’ button on the keyboard to choose him. Try choosing him 10 times and see how many times he’s successful at robbing a ship.

See, he was able to rob the ship most of the time but not every time.

[Press the space bar to continue]

In the game, you will get to choose which of three pirates you want to rob the next ship. Press ‘1’ to pick the pirate with the red beard. Press ‘2’ to pick white beard. Press ‘3’ to pick black beard.

Try picking a pirate now!

That pirate was successful at robbing the ship!

[Press the space bar to continue]

This pirate was not successful at robbing the ship!

[Press the space bar to continue]

You’ll stop at these 6 places on your journey.

[Press the space bar to continue]

How good a pirate is at robbing ships will depend on the current place. Some pirates will have been to the place before, and will have more experience robbing ships there. So, they will be more successful at stealing gold and bringing it back to you.

[Press the space bar to continue]

How successful a pirate is at robbing ships can also change in a place. Ships may hear about the pirates coming and will improve their defenses. This will make it more difficult to rob them. Ships may also hear that the pirate currently robbing ships is not very good at it and will lower their defenses. This will make it easier to rob them.

Things are always changing on the high seas! So, try your best to pay attention!

[Press the space bar to continue]

Sometimes you’ll be asked if you’ve seen a ship before. You will use the 5,6,7,8 buttons on your keyboard to respond.

If you definitely did not the ship, pick the the big red thumbs down by pressing 5. If you don’t think you saw it but aren’t sure, then pick the small red thumbs down by pressing 6. If you think you might have seen it, then pick the small green thumbs up by pressing 7. If you definitely did see this ship before, then pick the big thumb green thumbs up by pressing 8. If you remember correctly, then you’ll get a gold coin!

[Press the space bar to begin the next phase of the experiment]

.

If you don’t make your choice fast enough, you’ll have to wait a few seconds before you can make another one. You can’t win more gold. You just have to sit and wait.

[Press the space bar to continue]

Again, you have two important things to do:

1. Pick the pirate who you think will be most successful at robbing the ship.

2. Remember which place your chosen pirate robbed a ship and what item that ship carried.

Both are important in determining how much bonus money you’ll win


Let’s try a practice game. The game will start by showing you the pirates. First pick a pirate using the 1, 2, 3 button on your keyboard. When you are shown the ship with the item it was selling, try to remember the place you’re in by making up a story. You only have 3 seconds to pick a pirate, so please make a choice quickly! If you are too slow, you’ll have to wait a bit during the time out. Don’t feel rushed, but please do try to make a choice every time.

How good a pirate is at robbing a ship will change depending on the location they are in and how good the defenses are of the ship. This is just a practice game, so you’re not playing for money. You’ll receive a bag which may or may not contain gold coins. In the real game, though, you’ll be able to see whether or not you received the gold coins. Good luck, remember press 1 to help red beard, 2 to help white beard, and 3 to help black beard

[Press the space bar to begin the practice game]
